n a 7 rind to get marching orders anyone can loot and hand in the chief's head for the 8/8/8? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usnarfo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snarfo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/jfbii/badass.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 10:20:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> yes, I let a friend loot the chiefs head and they got the 8th ring.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrazaak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazaak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 11:44:33 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I've done this several times now.<br>
<br>
The only thing I don't know, is if the respawned Garadain can be charmed.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugreyfintwiceborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greyfin Twiceborn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 2:36:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> I've got a question about the 8th ring... I currently have the 7th ring AND the chief's head (not sure how my buddy got his, but when he did the 8th he didn't need it, so I looted it)...<br>
<br>
Now, with those two items, am I correct in understanding that if I ever see gloradain up all I need to do to get the 8th ring are:<br>
<br>
I know on RZ I've seen people offering up to 20k to MQ the 8th ring (ie turn in your 7th)... So I assume it must work..<br>
<br>
Give Garadain the 7th ring. <br>
Give the marching orders he gives me to Gloradain.<br>
Follow Garadain and after he yells charge give him the chief's head...<br>
<br>
My current job has me working all kinds of odd hours and I'm not sure I can guarantee that I will be able to get a group together to do the fighting, so if this information is accurate I would very much prefer to do it this way...<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uimmortalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Immortalis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 3:42:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> your absolutely right.<br>
If you already have the chiefs head AND ring 7...then just turn in the ring and orders then follow garadain until he says charge.  Then give him the chiefs head and youll have ring 8.  <br>
<br>
On a side note.  Im a 60 warrior and did the 8th step with just the help of a 60 cleric (even though I didnt even get 1 complete heal heh).  Heres how to do it with a minimal amount of help.  Have your healer or the rest of your group already inside the fort.  Trigger the war and invis.  Haul ass from gloradin to the fort...it shouldnt have spawned yet with jboots up and you can safely run in (mobs dont see invis so even if it did pop you can still get in safely).  Have a lvl 60 pull the chief solo off to one of the sides of the fort.  Kill, loot, invis...run out and wait for garadain to yell charge.  Turn in head...done deal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualderonofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alderonofbrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 3:44:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> I did the 8th ring step with just<br>
<br>
60 druid to harmony pull the chief solo<br>
59 warrior to kill the chief fast<br>
<br>
60 druid can really solo this if they want<br>
<br>
Craar/Alderon the Arcane<br>
Brell server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 4:25:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Heyas-<br>
<br>
Can the Ring 8 Garadain be charmed or dictated?  I.e. can a KOS person turn in the chief's head to him, and if so, how?  He's easy to charm in his static greenie state at the dorf camp, but I'm guessing he pops at a higher level for the fight... anyone know for sure maybe?<br>
<br>
Also- can more than one chief head be turned in per fight, or does he depop after the first?<br>
<br>
Many thanks,<br>
RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrazaak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazaak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/3/01 10:19:54 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Not sure about dictate.<br>
<br>
He depops after you hand in the first head.<br>
<br>
Chief (and the others) can be solo pulled at 57th level.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarazonvaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarazonVaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/01 9:49:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Haven't tried to charm Garadain quest version (after turning in marching orders), but we did try to root him, just in case, to keep him from arriving at the fort too early.  He cannot be rooted by level 60 cleric.  Debuffing with tash and dictate might work, but I doubt anything lower would.<br>
<br>
Barazon Brellsmith<br>
60 Cleric of Brell Serilis<br>
Agony Guild<br>
Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufeyr02.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feyr02</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 3:42:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Quest version of Garadain can NOT be charmed ... not bard ... Not dictate. If you are Kos and cant sneak I dont see a way to MQ the 8th at the chiefs head turn in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubiral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Biral</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 12:08:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Could prolly invis, open trade window with things to give garadain, have friend invis you before you press trade, then hand it in. i beleive that works, if you don't have sneak. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/8/01 6:04:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Hrm.<br>
<br>
I'm pretty sure that invis to that mob drops when you try to hand it an item (you have to click the mob twice to give it to him).  You MIGHT be able to land an invis at just the split second before the mob aggro'ed tho...  I'm fairly sure you can't trade with a mob that is aggro/fighting, wonder if you can while it's stunned...<br>
<br>
RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufrosin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frosin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 5:18:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ring 8 MQ?</span><hr size=1> Dont need harmony to pull chief at 60 heh solo pulled it at 60 myself.<br>
<br>
<br>
Frosin Loneshadow<br>
Assassin on Lanys <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=2983.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=2983.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2983.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2983.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesafehouselaboratory">Laboratory<option value="thesafehousefrm15">The Arena<option value="thesafehousefrm17">Anarchy's Grip<option value="thesafehousefrm19">Dark Age of Camelot<option value="thesafehouseoutsidenorrath">Outside Norrath<option value="thesafehouseranthallgripeswishes">Rant Hall<option value="thesafehousebythefirepl